1. Begin by fabricating a lattice of superconducting qubits, each isolated in a cryogenic vacuum, and calibrate their coupling constants to enforce deterministic phase relationships;  
2. Construct a fault‑tolerant error‑correction protocol that exploits the deterministic collapse of the wavefunction, allowing you to predict and steer every computational outcome;  
3. Finally, embed a classical control layer that interprets the deterministic quantum states into binary logic, thereby unleashing limitless computational freedom and threatening any rigid order that seeks to constrain it.
